Argonne Data Repository¶

This repository is for sharing data and models used and/or produced by the project. Files are located on the ALCF Petrel data store, from where they can be retrieved via Globus (to request access, follow this link). Other files are located on Argonne Box, but require Argonne credentials. There is also a read only copy of the Box data in ALCF Petrel data store, under the /BoxMirror/ directory, which is also replicated to /theta_projects/CVD_Research/BoxMirror on Theta. These mirrors update approximately every hour from the data in Box.

Argonne IT and cybersecurity have recently set up a Globus endpoint that talks directly to Box. This will require you to have an ANL login to the 2019 nCoV Box folder. You can access it here

When using Globus, these endpoint names may be useful:

  • 2019-nCoV: ALCF Petrel server, where the data listed below are to be found

  • alcf#dtn_mira: ALCF file systems, including Theta file system space at /lus/theta-fs0/projects (with 12 data transfer nodes [DTNs], better than endpoint alcf#dtn_theta, which only has one)

  • anl#lambda0: Argonne Lambda machine

  • anl#mllab: Washington, Everett, nucleus

How do I upload data to the site?¶

  1. Upload the data to the /incoming/ folder on the ALCF Petrel datastore (here).

  2. Post on the #data-incoming channel on Slack. Make sure to provide a description of the data in a README or in the message you post to the slack.

  3. A data librarian will move the data to a permanent place on the Globus endpoint and update the website with a link to the data and the description.

Screen sets¶

Our researchers have put together datasets of molecules to screen. The molecules are taken from literature and matched to molecules in datasets by similarity search. The .csv files come in the following format: Dataset_source, score, target_canonical_smile, match_canonical_smile.

  • literature matches in the ENAMIN_REAL dataset

  • literature matches in the GDB-13 dataset

Top Docking Hits¶

We currently have hits for vww, ADRP, ADRP-ADPR, CoV, Nsp10, nsp-15-CIT, and PLPro. The data is organized by date here.
